text: Altaic languages is a hypothetical language family that was proposed to include the Turkic, Mongolian, and Tungusic. Altaic may also refer to: * Altai Mountains, a mountain range in Central and East Asia where Russia, China, Mongolia, and Kazakhstan come together ==See also== *Altay (disambiguation) *Ural–Altaic languages Category:Language and nationality disambiguation pages
title: Altaic (disambiguation)
